HEADWORD: Selvagee
<hw>Sel`va*gee"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>
<def>A skein or hank of rope yarns wound round with yarns or marline, --
used for stoppers, straps, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Selve</ent>⟦br⟧
